  protein: 16 g
  sodium: 2 g
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and chop each half into four pieces. Separate the onion layers. Remove the core from the @yellow pepper{1} and cut into slices 1cm wide. Cut the top off the @aubergine{1}, cut it lengthways into slices about 1cm wide, then cut the slices in half.

Put your onion, pepper and half the @plum tomatoes{4} on a #baking tray{} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{} grind. Sprinkle over the @dried Italian herbs{1.5%tsp}, a glug of @olive oil{} and pop on the top shelf of your oven to cook for ~{20%minutes}. Meanwhile, cut the top and bottom off the @courgette{1}, then cut in half lengthways. Cut each half lengthways again into four strips. Chop the strips into batons about the length of your little finger.

Slice the remaining @plum tomatoes{4} in half through the equator. Roughly chop half the @basil{1/2%bunch}. Put your tomatoes in a #bowl{} with the @balsamic vinegar{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{} grind and mix together. Leave to the side. Cut the @ciabatta{1} in half through the middle and keep to the side.

Put a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a glug of @oil{glug} and cook your aubergine slices (they need to be in a single layer, so do this in two batches and add more oil when cooking the second batch if you need to). Sprinkle over a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and a good grind of @black pepper{} grind and fry for ~{3-4%minutes} on each side until charred and soft. Once cooked, remove your aubergine to a #plate{} and cover with #foil{} to keep warm.

There shouldn't be any oil left in the pan but if there is just wipe it out with some #kitchen paper{}. Put the pan back on medium heat and season your courgette with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{} grind. Cook in one layer without any oil (do this in two batches as well if you need to!). Dry-fry on one side for ~{3-4%minutes} until slightly charred, then turn the courgette over and cook on the other side for another ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from the pan.

Once your onion, pepper and tomatoes are cooked, take them out of your oven. Crumble over the @feta cheese{1} and add in your chopped basil. Stir everything together and cover with foil to keep warm. Turn your grill to high and place your ciabatta halves underneath. Grill them for ~{2-3%minutes} on each side until nicely toasted, then remove. Cut the @garlic clove{1} in half and rub the cut sides on each ciabatta half.

Put one ciabatta half on each plate, layer on your aubergine slices then pile your veggie-feta mixture on top followed by your courgette. Finish with your balsamic tomatoes and any leftover juices. Tear over your remaining basil and enjoy!

> The definition of deconstructed is 'to reduce something to its constituent parts'. We wouldn't say there is any reduction going on here - this dish is such a showstopper, that we wanted to let everything from the ratatouille and feta to the garlicky ciabatta, absolutely shine!